<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1806,2013]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,1842,1868]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
This species differs from the other species of the family occurring in the freshwaters of the country (Atlantic) by the following combination of characters: gill rakers very numerous, over 100 on lower limb of first gill arch (vs. usually less than 
<quantity box="[488,544,1914,1941]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.35" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="in" value="25.0">25 in</quantity>
the other species); and maxilla long, with its posterior tip reaching to or slightly beyond the preopercular margin (vs. maxilla short, with its tip not reaching the preopercular margin).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
